<p><a href="http://projecteuler.net/problem=3">Problem 3</a> asks:</p>
<blockquote><p>What is the largest prime factor of the number 600&#8239;851&#8239;475&#8239;143?</p></blockquote>
<p>Here&rsquo;s what I did in Java:</p>
<pre>
public class Problem3 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        long number = 600851475143L;
        int result = 0;
        for (int factor = 2; factor &lt;= number; factor++) {
            if (number % factor == 0) {
                result = factor;
                number /= factor;
                factor = 2;
            }
        }
        System.out.println(result);
    }
}
</pre>
<p>This required a little more thought to write efficiently, but my solution turned out very simple so it&rsquo;s easy to follow.</p>
